    genomic underpinnings of microbiome dynamics under extreme
    selective pressures. Low intestinal microbial diversity, often
    leading to domination of the intestine by a single organism, is
    associated with poor outcomes following hematopoietic cell
    transplantation (HCT). Understanding how certain organisms achieve
    domination in the intestine is limited by current metagenomic
    sequencing technologies, which are typically unable to reconstruct
    complete genome drafts without bacterial isolation and culture.
    Recently, we developed a metagenomic read cloud sequencing
    approach that provides significantly improved genome drafts for
    individual organisms compared to conventional short-read
    sequencing methods. Here, we apply read cloud sequencing to four
    longitudinal stool samples collected from an HCT patient before
    and after heavy antibiotic exposure. During this time period, the
    patient experienced Escherichia coli gut domination and an E. coli
    bloodstream infection. We find that read clouds enable the
