    Our long-term sampling strategy and high-resolution multi-omics
    analyses of FMT donors and recipients reveal adaptive ecological
    processes as the main driver of microbial colonization outcomes
    after FMT. We also show that high-fitness donor microbial
    populations are significantly enriched in metabolic pathways that
    are responsible for the biosynthesis of nucleotides, essential
    amino acids, and micronutrients, independent of taxonomy. To
