    maintenance, disease risk and progression, and biochemical
    responses to perturbations, such as diet or drugs. We list methods
    for identifying, quantifying, and tracking strains, utilizing
    high-throughput sequencing along with other molecular and
    ``culturomics'' technologies. Finally, we discuss implications of
    population studies in bridging experimental gaps and leading to a
